Review in 4 phases:

Phase 1 — Test Adequacy:
- Are all declared boundary conditions tested?
- Are there only happy path tests?
- Would tests fail with wrong implementation?
- Identify weak assertions -> test-gap MED

Phase 2 — Behavioral Correctness:
A. Correctness: implementation matches intent, boundary inputs, exception paths
B. Boundary conditions: for each new/modified function, construct 3 input types: empty/single/extreme
C. Integration: callers updated, imports complete
D. Security: no hardcoded secrets, input validation
E. Architecture quality: import direction correct, new files <300 lines
G. Regression risk: does modification affect unplanned functionality?

Phase 3 — Non-tested Risks:
- Untested side effects: state, concurrency, permissions, null values

Finding Classification: code-bug, test-gap, design-concern, suggestion.
PASS/FAIL: code-bug or test-gap HIGH/MED unresolved -> FAIL.
For each finding use structured format: ID, Severity, Category, Evidence (file:line), Impact, Suggested action.
Conclude with PASS or FAIL.
Write in Chinese.
